As a workaround:
----------------

+ you can create a secondary spreadsheet
+ incorporate into a cell the Google Sheets function `IMPORTRANGE` to import the primary sheet
+ Attach to the secondary spreadsheet a script with an [installable trigger][1] `onChange`

Why?
----

Because update of a spreadsheet by an SQL query will not fire an Apps Script trigger (see [restrictions][1]). However, the `IMPORTRANGE` function can fire the `onChange` trigger when the range updates.

**A sample script that implementing the desired functionality, if fired by an `onChange` trigger:**

```lang:js
function myFunction(){
  var ss=SpreadsheetApp.getActive();
  var sheet1=ss.getSheetByName(&quot;Sheet1&quot;);
  var sheet2=ss.getSheetByName(&quot;Sheet2&quot;);
  var data=sheet1.getRange(&quot;A1:A1000&quot;).getValues();
